<quantity id="4CF19B6992457727FB7CFE2EFB6DBE50" box="[1154,1276,510,539]" metricMagnitude="7" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.25" pageId="21" pageNumber="174" unit="km" value="42500.0">42,500 km</quantity>
², and should be classified as “Least Concern” (LC), following 
<bibRefCitation id="EF984B7D92457727FD5FFDF2FCA9BE77" author="IUCN Standards and Petitions Subcommittee &amp; Cambridge, UK" box="[673,824,546,572]" pageId="21" pageNumber="174" refId="ref19879" refString="IUCN Standards and Petitions Subcommittee (2017) Guidelines for Using the IUCN Red List Categories and Criteria. Version 13 (March 2017). Prepared by the IUCN species survival commission. IUCN Council, Gland, Switzerland and Cambridge, UK, 108 pp. Available from: http: // cmsdocs. s 3. amazonaws. com / RedList Guidelines. pdf (Accessed 9 February 2019)" type="book" year="2017">IUCN (2017)</bibRefCitation>
categories. In 
<collectingRegion id="49CDF86E92457727FC1EFDF1FBB2BE70" box="[992,1059,545,571]" country="Brazil" name="Bahia" pageId="21" pageNumber="174">Bahia</collectingRegion>
, this species has been found in the conservation units “ 
<collectingCounty id="62D74E0092457727FE9BFD95FD26BE14" box="[357,695,581,607]" pageId="21" pageNumber="174">Estação Ecológica Pau-Brasil</collectingCounty>
”, “ 
<collectingMunicipality id="6BD2ACF692457727FD28FD95FA94BE14" box="[726,1285,581,607]" pageId="21" pageNumber="174">Reserva Particular do Patrimônio Natural Veracel</collectingMunicipality>
” and “ 
<location id="8ED6605792457727FAB1FD95FEDCBEC9" LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:03A0879A92437727FF76F8FBFAD1B84E:8ED6605792457727FAB1FD95FEDCBEC9" county="Estacao Ecologica Pau-Brasil" municipality="Reserva Particular do Patrimonio Natural Veracel" name="Reserva Biologica de Una" pageId="21" pageNumber="174" stateProvince="Bahia">Reserva Biológica de Una</location>
” but also within private properties
</materialsCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C313650792457727FF43FD5BFAD1B84E" pageId="21" pageNumber="174" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BB6368C92457727FF43FD5BFAD1B84E" blockId="21.[136,1452,158,1030]" pageId="21" pageNumber="174">
<emphasis id="B97DEA9E92457727FF43FD5BFE99BEEE" bold="true" box="[189,264,651,677]" pageId="21" pageNumber="174">Notes:</emphasis>
— 
<taxonomicName id="4C094D0F92457727FEDAFD5BFD9ABEEE" authorityName="De Candolle" authorityYear="1828" box="[292,523,651,677]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Bertolonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="21" pageNumber="174" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="maculata">
<emphasis id="B97DEA9E92457727FEDAFD5BFD9ABEEE" box="[292,523,651,677]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="174">Bertolonia maculata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
occurs in the states of 
<collectingRegion id="49CDF86E92457727FCE2FD5BFCCDBEEE" box="[796,860,651,677]" country="Brazil" name="Bahia" pageId="21" pageNumber="174">Bahia</collectingRegion>
and 
<collectingRegion id="49CDF86E92457727FC67FD5BFBACBEEE" box="[921,1085,651,677]" country="Brazil" name="Espirito Santo" pageId="21" pageNumber="174">Espírito Santo</collectingRegion>
. In 
<collectingRegion id="49CDF86E92457727FB92FD5BFB3EBEEE" box="[1132,1199,651,677]" country="Brazil" name="Bahia" pageId="21" pageNumber="174">Bahia</collectingRegion>
, the species is widely distributed in lowland rainforests (
<figureCitation id="13322A0992457727FDF4FD7EFDF8BE82" box="[522,617,686,713]" captionStart="FIGURE 13" captionStartId="19.[136,229,1730,1752]" captionTargetBox="[346,1239,435,1693]" captionTargetId="figure-140@19.[340,1247,425,1706]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="FIGURE 13. Distributions of species of Bertolonia in Bahia.A.Bertolonia linearifolia. B. Bertolonia maculata. C. Bertolonia marmorata. D. Bertolonia reginatoi. E. Bertolonia riocontensis. F. Bertolonia violacea. G. Bertolonia vitoriana." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6597718" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6597718/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="174">Fig. 13b</figureCitation>
) along the central and southern coast, with some specimens also collected inland, in this case in the southern region of the state, in low elevation areas (
<quantity id="4CF19B6992457727FC19FD01FBFBBEA7" box="[999,1130,721,748]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.75" metricValueMax="4.5" metricValueMin="1.0" pageId="21" pageNumber="174" unit="m" value="275.0" valueMax="450.0" valueMin="100.0">100–450 m</quantity>
), on rocky outcrops or at the base of trees (
<bibRefCitation id="EF984B7D92457727FEE3FD25FE49BF44" author="Baumgratz, J. F. A." box="[285,472,757,783]" pageId="21" pageNumber="174" pagination="69 - 213" refId="ref18783" refString="Baumgratz, J. F. A. (1990) O genero Bertolonia Raddi (Melastomataceae): revisao taxonomica e consideracoes anatomicas. Arquivos do Jardim Botanico do Rio de Janeiro - Serie Botanica 30: 69 - 213." type="journal article" year="1990">Baumgratz 1990</bibRefCitation>
). Collected with flowers and fruits between January and February, and June to November. 
<taxonomicName id="4C094D0F92457727FF76FCC8FEFBBF79" authorityName="De Candolle" authorityYear="1828" box="[136,362,792,818]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Bertolonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="21" pageNumber="174" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="maculata">
<emphasis id="B97DEA9E92457727FF76FCC8FEFBBF79" box="[136,362,792,818]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="174">Bertolonia maculata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be distinguished by the stem, petioles and hypanthium densely glandulose-villose (the trichomes 
<quantity id="4CF19B6992457727FF76FCEBFF68BF1D" box="[136,249,827,854]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.65" metricValueMax="4.0" metricValueMin="1.3" pageId="21" pageNumber="174" unit="mm" value="2.65" valueMax="4.0" valueMin="1.3">1.3–4 mm</quantity>
long), petals with an apiculate apex and anthers dehiscing through an introrse pore with thickened margins. It is closely related to 
<taxonomicName id="4C094D0F92457727FE76FC8FFDB4BF33" box="[392,549,863,888]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Bertolonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="21" pageNumber="174" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="marmorata">
<emphasis id="B97DEA9E92457727FE76FC8FFDB4BF33" box="[392,549,863,888]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="174">B. marmorata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and they differ mainly by the morphology of the anthers. 
<taxonomicName id="4C094D0F92457727FB3BFC8EFA3DBF33" authorityName="De Candolle" authorityYear="1828" box="[1221,1452,862,888]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Bertolonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="21" pageNumber="174" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="maculata">
<emphasis id="B97DEA9E92457727FB3BFC8EFA3DBF33" box="[1221,1452,862,888]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="174">Bertolonia maculata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has anthers with a flat or slightly undulate surface, and dehiscing through an introrse pore with thickened margins (
<emphasis id="B97DEA9E92457727FF6FFC75FF39BFF5" box="[145,168,933,958]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="174">vs</emphasis>
. undulate anthers with extrorse pores that do not have thickened margins). 
<taxonomicName id="4C094D0F92457727FBFEFC75FB77BFF4" authorityName="De Candolle" authorityYear="1828" box="[1024,1254,933,959]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Bertolonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="21" pageNumber="174" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="maculata">
<emphasis id="B97DEA9E92457727FBFEFC75FB77BFF4" box="[1024,1254,933,959]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="174">Bertolonia maculata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is also similar to 
<taxonomicName id="4C094D0F92457727FF76FC18FEC4BFA9" authorityName="Baumgratz" authorityYear="1990" box="[136,341,968,994]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Bertolonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="21" pageNumber="174" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="carmoi">
<emphasis id="B97DEA9E92457727FF76FC18FEC4BFA9" box="[136,341,968,994]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="174">Bertolonia carmoi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and differs from it by the petals with an apiculate apex (
<emphasis id="B97DEA9E92457727FC1CFC19FB91BFA9" box="[994,1024,969,994]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="174">vs.</emphasis>
acuminate or acute in 
<taxonomicName id="4C094D0F92457727FAFDFC19FAE0BFA9" authorityName="Baumgratz" authorityYear="1990" box="[1283,1393,969,994]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Bertolonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="21" pageNumber="174" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="carmoi">
<emphasis id="B97DEA9E92457727FAFDFC19FAE0BFA9" box="[1283,1393,969,994]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="174">B. carmoi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) and unappendaged anthers (
<emphasis id="B97DEA9E92457727FE70FC3CFE3DB84E" box="[398,428,1004,1029]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="174">vs.</emphasis>
dorsally bilobed in 
<taxonomicName id="4C094D0F92457727FD79FC3CFD65B84E" authorityName="Baumgratz" authorityYear="1990" box="[647,756,1004,1029]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Bertolonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="21" pageNumber="174" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="carmoi">
<emphasis id="B97DEA9E92457727FD79FC3CFD65B84E" box="[647,756,1004,1029]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="174">B. carmoi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) For more details see 
<bibRefCitation id="EF984B7D92457727FC17FC3CFB23B84E" author="Baumgratz, J. F. A." box="[1001,1202,1003,1030]" pageId="21" pageNumber="174" pagination="69 - 213" refId="ref18783" refString="Baumgratz, J. F. A. (1990) O genero Bertolonia Raddi (Melastomataceae): revisao taxonomica e consideracoes anatomicas. Arquivos do Jardim Botanico do Rio de Janeiro - Serie Botanica 30: 69 - 213." type="journal article" year="1990">Baumgratz (1990)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<tableCitation id="C68B033792457727FB19FC3BFAABB84E" box="[1255,1338,1003,1029]" captionStart="TABLE 1" captionStartId="6.[136,224,623,649]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="TABLE 1. Selected morphological characters scored for species in Bertolonia that occur in the state of Bahia, Brazil. “GP”= Glandulose-punctate; “GV”= Glandulose-villose." httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/DF76660492567734FF76FDBFF843BEC2" pageId="21" pageNumber="174" tableUuid="DF76660492567734FF76FDBFF843BEC2">Table 1</tableCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
</treatment>
